app.js
	Application entry point, to load configuration files and so
config.json
	Configuraton file containing access keys for Amazon web servises (AWS)
package.json
	JSON file containing application discription, version, dependencies and all
./node_modules
	Ignore this directory, automatically downloaded for resolving dependencies of the application.
./app
	Application development directory <- all the code goes here
	./public
		Can also be mostly Ignored, expect for 'js' folder, contains 'twitter bootstrap', jquery and other scripts, public images, css styling sheets, jade pages for login and registration systems
		./js
		Javascript files, can make scence with file names
	./server
		All most all the application logic and routings will be here 